desc:MCP Ambisonic Scene Mirror
//
// Bundled with the ReaperMCP extension (Batch S1). Reflects an ACN-ordered HOA soundfield across one
// of the three principal planes by applying the exact per-ACN-channel sign pattern of that reflection.
// A reflection of the sound scene is a pure per-channel polarity flip on the real spherical harmonics,
// so this is exact and order-independent (any order, up to 64 channels). Zero third-party dependency
// (JSFX ships with REAPER); complements the plug-in-driven spatial.rotate_scene.
//
// Driven by spatial.mirror_scene, which discovers the "Reflection plane" slider by name and sets it:
//   0  Left-Right   swap L <-> R  (reflect across the front/back vertical plane)  -> flip m < 0
//   1  Front-Back   swap front <-> back                                           -> flip per (-1)^..
//   2  Up-Down      swap up <-> down (reflect across the horizontal plane)        -> flip per (-1)^(l+|m|)
//
// Real SH (ACN/SN3D) parity, channel k with degree l=floor(sqrt(k)), order m=k-l*l-l, am=|m|:
//   Left-Right (azimuth phi -> -phi): sin(m phi) channels (m<0) flip; cos channels unchanged.
//   Front-Back (phi -> pi-phi):       cos channels *= (-1)^m; sin channels *= (-1)^(am+1).
//   Up-Down   (theta -> pi-theta):    all channels *= (-1)^(l+am)  (elevation parity, azimuth-agnostic).
// Normalization (SN3D vs N3D) is irrelevant to a sign flip, so this is correct for either.

slider1:plane=0<0,2,1{Left-Right,Front-Back,Up-Down}>Reflection plane

